{"action": "input", "code": "def replace_color_upper_right(input_grid: np.ndarray, position: Tuple[int, int], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replaces the color with input color in upper-right direction of input position in input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    position: A tuple of two integers representing the position in the input grid.\n    color: An integer representing the color to be replaced.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    row, col = position\n    while row >= 0 and col < input_grid.shape[1] and (input_grid[row][col] == color):\n        input_grid[row][col] = color\n        row -= 1\n        col += 1\n    return input_grid\ndef identity(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the input grid as is.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return input_grid\ndef replace_color_upper_left(input_grid: np.ndarray, position: Tuple[int, int], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replaces the color with input color in upper-left direction of input position in input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    position: A tuple of two integers representing the position in the input grid.\n    color: An integer representing the color to be replaced.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    row, col = position\n    while row >= 0 and col >= 0 and (input_grid[row][col] == color):\n        input_grid[row][col] = color\n        row -= 1\n        col -= 1\n    return input_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = identity(input_grid)\n    position_first, position_last = find_first_last_non_black(input_grid)\n    color = get_first_element_last_line(input_grid)\n    output_grid = replace_color_upper_left(output_grid, position_first, color)\n    output_grid = replace_color_upper_right(output_grid, position_last, color)\n    return output_grid\ndef find_first_last_non_black(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the first and last non-black element in the penultimate line of the input grid and returns their positions.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple of two integers representing the positions of the first and last non-black element in the penultimate line of the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    penultimate_line = input_grid[-2]\n    first_non_black = np.where(penultimate_line != black)[0][0]\n    last_non_black = np.where(penultimate_line != black)[0][-1]\n    return (first_non_black, last_non_black)\ndef get_first_element_last_line(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the first element of the last line in the input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the first element of the last line in the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return input_grid[-1][0]", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = `same as input grid`(input_grid)\n    position_first, position_last = `find the frist and last non black element in Penultimate line of input grid, return their positions`(input_grid)\n    color = `return the first element of last line in input grid`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = `replace the line with input color in upper-left direction of input position in input grid `(output_grid, position_first, color)\n    output_grid = `replace the line with input color in upper-right direction of input position in input grid `(output_grid, position_last, color)\n\n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "def replace_color_upper_right(input_grid: np.ndarray, position: Tuple[int, int], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n 